Demo Remote Network and VPN Requirements:
  • 1) Cisco 1811w uses IPSec over UDP and requires the following ports to be open:
  • * ESP port 50
  • * UDP port 500
  • * Port 4500 (NAT)
  • 2) When using the Cisco 1811w, avoid the following subnets:
  • * 10.0.1.0/24
  • * 10.0.2.0/24
  • * 10.0.3.0/24
  • * 10.0.4.0/24
  • * 10.1.1.0/24
  • 3) If IPSec over UDP does not work, try the Cisco Software VPN Client which utilizes IPSec over
  • TCP (port 443)
  • 4) VPN credentials are dynamically generated and displayed in the UI
  • 5) You must wait until the demonstration session has started before you can establish your VPN
  • session
  • Bandwidth Requirements
  • 1) Demo Remote requires at least a 768kbps connection (upload and download)
  • 2) Audio and video conferences need at least a 1.5Mbps (upload and download)
  • 3) Insufficient bandwidth may cause poor voice and video quality, improperly functioning features,
  • and dropped VPN connections
  • 4) Users should check connectivity and available bandwidth before using a demo. The Demo Remote
  • UI includes a utility and instructions to perform this test. Refer to the Demo Remote Release Notes
  • and click the test link in the UI to view the Bandwidth Test documentation.
